   <titleInfo>
      <title>Letter, William A. Huddard near Knoxville, Tenn. to his father in Ohio, 1863 December 20</title>
   </titleInfo>
   <abstract>In this letter, dated December 20, 1863, William A. Huddard, stationed near Knoxville, Tenn., writes to his father in Ohio, discussing recent military operations around Knoxville. He explains that his brigade was sent to the "Front, being placed on the extreme left to hold the Gap between Clinch and House mountains." Also, he complains that he is "getting tired of this place," as he had not "seen a paper since leaving Chattanooga."</abstract>
